<br>
Dromel says, in Elvish, 'No we are camping the undead jeste'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'Ahhh'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'You do realize that's what I've been doing?'<br>
Dromel says, in Elvish, 'Good for you'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'Wow, I haven't run across folk like this yet'<br>
Dromel says, in Elvish, 'Like what?'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'Camp jumping and such'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'Dromel, would you refer me to an officer in your guild?'<br>
Dromel says, in Elvish, 'Yeah talk to Braxom'<br>
Braxom is an officer of Winds of Destiny<br>
Dromel says, in Elvish, 'He don't speak elvish to well though'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'no doubt'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'Well everyone speaks Elvish on the boards'<br>
Dromel says, in Elvish, 'If your expecting me to jump up and leave after making the trip here your daft. And btw there are no recognized camps on this server. So if you find him first more power to ya. But if we do to bad.'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'As you wish. It is probably yo much of me to expect honor from everyone'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'Still, guilds generally insist honor from their members. I'll find out if Winds folows that path as well'<br>
Dromel says, in Elvish, 'Go ahead its not gonna help you any'<br>
Dromel says, in Elvish, 'Do it see how much it help'<br>
Dromel says, in Elvish, 'I cam here fully expecting to be here for A LONG time im not just leaving cause some disrespectfull upstart wants to start crap with me'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'I don't need the help in that regard sir paladin. I beleive you are the ones that suffer'<br>
Dromel says, in Elvish, 'Paldins dont dual weild moron im a warrior'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'Ahh so you are. That would explain little though. Even warriors are prone to respect others'<br>
Dromel says, in Elvish, 'Depends on your alignment really'<br>
You say, in Elvish, 'No, depends on the player, really'<br>
<br>
Now please draw your own conclusions. Personally, I find this basic lack of player respect to be the worst part of any multi-player game. Not to mention, when you bully your way through a blue server, you're pretty much announcing yourself as a pussy. Since Braxom is an officer in Winds of Destiny, I might conclude that Winds of Destiny as a guild sanctions this sort of disrespectful attitude and offensive play style. I do extend the benefit of the doubt though, as many guilds are simply grabbing all the players they can right now as part of thier building process. If that's the case, WoD you got some weeding to do. I'm interested in hearing from WoD on this matter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uveloxiavoluptuous.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veloxia Voluptuous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/1/02 10:58:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Winds of Destiny?</span><hr size=1> i like how you brought this up, although, have you spoken to anyone in their guild yet? have you posted on their site? if so a link to their site would be nice. personally i dont know any guilds' sites other than the 2 i have been in on FV <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
